As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires:
"Board" means the Kentucky Board of Hairdressers and Cosmetologists, created in KRS 317A.030;
"Esthetician" means a person who is licensed by the board to engage in esthetic practices in the Commonwealth of Kentucky;
"Esthetic practices" means one (1) or more of the following acts:
Giving facials, including consultation and skin analysis;
Providing makeup artistry, including corrective and camouflage techniques;
Giving skin care;
Removing facial hair;
Beautifying or cleaning the body with the use of cosmetic preparations, antiseptics, tonics, lotions, or creams; or
Providing preoperative and postoperative esthetic skin care, either referred by or supervised by a medical professional;
Except when these acts are performed incident to:
Treatment of an illness or a disease;
Work as a student in a board approved school;
Work without compensation from the person receiving the service; or
Work performed by a licensed massage therapist; and
"Esthetic salon" means a place where an esthetician performs esthetic practices.
